      <bioghist id="aspace_65f548bc995d82a96179ffa65f1057e6">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p>Hinson was a Methodist minister who spent most of his career pastoring churches in North
            Carolina.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_89430fb9d7bf0b2fc9ebc607639eee36">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>The collection documenting the life and religious writings of O.I. Hinson consists of 45
            handwritten sermons and outlines of sermons by Hinson, [ca. 1914]-1932; 20 letters
            written between 1937-1939 and 1946-1947, from Hinson to his brother, Jeremias Enos
            Hinson; a photograph of Hinson; and a small number of clippings and other miscellaneous
            papers.</p>
      </scopecontent>
